ww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMeta%3C%2Fa%3E%20want%20to%20make%20our%20social%20media%20accounts%20immortal%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20was%20granted%20a%20patent%20in%20late%20December%20that%20outlines%20how%20a%20large%20language%20model%20can%20%26quot%3Bsimulate%26quot%3B%20a%20person's%20social%20media%20activity%2C%20such%20as%20responding%20to%20content%20posted%20by%20real%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20language%20model%20may%20be%20used%20for%20simulating%20the%20user%20when%20the%20user%20is%20absent%20from%20the%20social%20networking%20system%2C%20for%20example%2C%20when%20the%20user%20takes%20a%20long%20break%20or%20if%20the%20user%20is%20deceased%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20patent%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-cto-andrew-bosworth-reality-labs-all-hands-meeting-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAndrew%20Bosworth%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Meta's%20CTO%2C%20is%20listed%20as%20the%20primary%20author%20of%20the%20patent%2C%20which%20was%20first%20filed%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20no%20plans%20to%20move%20forward%20with%20this%20example%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20Meta%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20patent%2C%20Meta%20lays%20out%20why%20it%20thinks%20people%20might%20need%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20no%20longer%20posting%20online%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20that's%20because%20you%20need%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbricking-your-phone-analog-movement-the-new-dry-january-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebreak%20from%20social%20media%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%E2%80%A6%20you%20%E2%80%A6%20die%20%E2%80%94%20your%20followers'%20user%20experience%20will%20be%20affected.%20In%20short%2C%20they'll%20miss%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20impact%20on%20the%20users%20is%20much%20more%20severe%20and%20permanent%20if%20that%20user%20is%20deceased%20and%20can%20never%20re