%20be%20awful.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20aren't%20the%20only%20ones%20referencing%20the%20pandemic.%20In%20a%20popular%20X%20article%2C%20HyperWrite%20CEO%20Matt%20Shumer%20wrote%20that%20AI's%20impact%20on%20work%20would%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmatt-shumer-something-big-is-happening-essay-ai-disruption-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bmuch%2C%20much%20bigger%20than%20Covid.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20years%2C%20the%20question%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fartificial-intelligence-layoffs-big-tech-workers-jobs-careers-rmicrosoft-amazon-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI-driven%20layoffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20haunted%20workers%20at%20Big%20Tech%20companies%2C%20many%20of%20which%20went%20on%20a%20hiring%20spree%20during%20the%20pandemic.%20While%20it's%20often%20impossible%20to%20boil%20job%20loss%20down%20a%20single%20reason%2C%20many%20suspect%20productivity%20gains%20from%20AI%20and%20ballooning%20capex%20spending%20are%20fueling%20the%20cuts.%20Some%20business%20leaders%20have%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flist-companies-replacing-human-employees-with-ai-layoffs-workforce-reductions%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eexplicitly%20cited%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20announcing%20layoffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20tech%20leaders%20describe%20smaller%20teams%20working%20more%20efficiently.%20On%20a%20recent%20earnings%20call%2C%20Meta%20CEO%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20said%20one%20engineer%20could%20now%20do%20the%20work%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-says-ai-letting-one-employee-do-work-of-teams-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20whole%20team%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20thanks%20to%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20AI%20productivity%20grows%2C%20so%20have%20complaints%20of%20AI%20fatigue.%20Software%20engineer%20Siddhant%20Khare%20penned%20a%20lengthy%20essay%20about%20growing